contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization. Supersedes contactPoints.

member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be  members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.  Supersedes members, musicGroupMember. Inverse property: memberOf.

founder.description: A person who founded this organization. Supersedes founders.

photo.description: A photograph of this place. Supersedes photos.

makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person. Inverse property: offeredBy.

seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person  (demand).

additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the  entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there  is no matching property in schema.org.  Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific  schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width,  http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically  expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using  the generic property/value mechanism.

department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that  organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls,  logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery  with a cafe.

subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the  second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department'  property. Inverse property: parentOrganization.

review.description: A review of the item. Supersedes reviews.

description.description: A short description of the item.

branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a  place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization  and used in structured URLs.  For example, in the URL  http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is  a branchCode for a particular branch.

hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place. Supersedes map, maps.

alumni.description: Alumni of an organization. Inverse property: alumniOf.

additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific  types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a  relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa  syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute  - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding  of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

award.description: An award won by or for this item. Supersedes awards.

image.description: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization  belongs. Inverse property: member.

menu.description: Either the actual menu or a URL of the menu.

mainEntityOfPage.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main  entity being described.  See background notes for details. Inverse property: mainEntity.

potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which  this thing would play an 'object' role.

hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be  Boolean, a URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards  compatibility) the strings Yes or No.

hasPOS.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

owns.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

employee.description: Someone working for this organization. Supersedes employees.

containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains. Inverse property: containsPlace.

containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.  Supersedes containedIn. Inverse property: containsPlace.

brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s)  maintained by an organization or business person.

currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted (in ISO 4217 currency format).

dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or  business person.

geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided. Supersedes  serviceArea.

globalLocationNumber.description: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as  International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization,  person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and  physical locations.

isicV4.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic  Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business  person, or place.

parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a branch of, if any.  Supersedes branchOf. Inverse property: subOrganization.

location.description: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization  is located, or where an action takes place.

naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a  particular organization or business person.

numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

legalName.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

openingHours.description: The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a  weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days  can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are  specified using a hyphen '-'. - Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We,  Th, Fr, Sa, Su. - Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as  15:00. - Here is an example: Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm. - If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as Monday  through Sunday, all day.

openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the  item.

foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US  or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.  Supersedes events.

sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's  identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Freebase page, or  official website.
